Newer VW group car have a possibility to turn on this sign on a MaxiDot and you don't need this sticker.

snippet.textDisplay: I would spend 30k on a more modern Maserati Ghibli or Quattroporte, like the 2014-2015 ones. It's only 5 years and millages on them are relatively low on the market, and there are plenty of s or sq4 models that can smoke the Panamera. Yes, it's not as nice, but you really do get a more modern and faster car, and Maserati will attract more attention than a 2012 Panamera. First-gen Panamera compares to a 2020 Panamera were drastic, but a 2014 Quattroporte or Ghibli compares to 2020 are not that much because they never fully redesigned it. No one will think a first-gen Panamera is cool, but Quattroporte is rarer and the exhaust can make people look at you if that's what you want.
